content.detailedDescription:
I was driving to work early morning to the wachung mountain area and a piece of that road i was on only had tree's never a light, that morning as i got onto that part of my trip i noticed a very, very bright light, but as i got within a block or so of it the lights went out.
i thought it was funny because it was still dark but moonlight would light the top of the tree line, so i got to where i thought the light was and i got out of the car and looked up over the trees and there was a craft roughly the size of an airliner.
it was silent and had wings in a steel look bent back and down but bird like with a body that looked kind of like the egyptian needle with hieroglyphics running down the body and a pointed front.
when i realized this was not anything i knew i panicked and my heart was pounding out of my chest then i jumped into my car and drove away as fast as i could and never looked back.
when arriving to my sore that i worked at i called my mom and told me to call the police and i called the local police department and they said they have had calls and would make a report.
since this took place such along time ago i'm not exactly sure what month or year, but it is my best guess i was 19 or 20 and i'm 60 now.
i told my family and some friends at the time and they all laughed at me and through the years when subject came up i would tell people , but a lot get funny or just don't believe you.
this craft was amazing and i don't think in most of your show's or any other shows i have ever heard of a ship described the way i saw it, so i finally decided to report it to you.
it will be etched in my mind forever!
content.summary: Puter gray bent winged craft above tree line with light on then off had egyptian hieroglyphics on the body of craft silent

content.detailedDescription:
My sister and i were sitting out on our front porch around 9:45 in the evening, when we spotted an orange red object that was maybe five miles east and south of our location. we watched it moving in what looked to us like a search pattern, and it was moving slowly,  changing directions and altitude multiple times. when it was north and east of our location, it appeared to 'pull the light cloud cover around it'  cloaking itself from our sight. it wasn't even a minute later, that two more of these objects appeared, also south east of us. these looked like they were duplicating the pattern and altitudes of the first one. here was a slight difference, the two paused several times as they were going north. when they reached the area here the firste one vanished, they moved upward into the clouds right where the first one had gone. we could still see three faint red/orange points of light in the clouds, then all three winked out like a light switch being thrown. it's not the first time we have been outside at night enjoying the air and seen glowing spherical balls of light south east of us. the ones we saw during the summer months stayed south of us, and moved east to west, then shot straight up. there was no sound, that we could hear while these objects were moving around where we could see them. we plan to get a digital camera, so that we can get poof, our friends think we are nuts, but we know what we have seen more than once.

    we plan to keep our eyes open and skywards, becase it is exciting to spot one of these red/orange spheres, then see it do something amazing (like take off at extreamly high speed, or just vanish.) we get a thrill when we see them, kind of like anticipation of some grand event.
content.summary: My sister, dorothy and i were sitting on our porch, and we saw three objects gloswing red orange travel slowly from south to north and east of out location. they appeared to be "searching" for something.

content.detailedDescription: My friend and i were traveling home on february 16, 2000 on highway 400 going south.  we noticed a bluish green light in the distance.  we continually watched the light because of the color.  as we got near the outlet mall, the light became 4 distinct bluish green lights in a horizontal line.  i thought it was a communication tower because it did not move.  as we approached the where hwy 53 crossed 400, i could see that the lights were too high to be a communication tower.  i then got excited because i thought it might be a blimp.  after about another 2 to 3 miles, we saw the object off to the right.  it was not 4 lights but two sets of 4 lights that formed a "v" shape.  i pulled off the highway at a clearing.  we watched the triangular object for about 1 or 2 minutes then it rotated about 90 degrees and moved towards us.  as it moved over us we could see every detail of the object.  it was a dark black or gray metallic object.  it had a smooth surface on the bottom with a reddish pipe like tube around the bottom.  there was a round portal like thing in the center like on a submarine.  on two sides there were chambers like a large ship has. i could see depth, but i could not determine how thick the object was.  the object moved towards cumming, ga.  this event took around 5 minutes from the time it rotated and started moving.  two days later i noticed a blister like bump on the end of my nose that bleed when i washed my face.  i didn't think much about it until the friend that was with me said the same thing happened to him.  this scared me because i thought of radiation poisoning.  a few days later the blister was gone.  i have no doubt that what i saw was not from this earth.  it would take antigravity to hover something that large that made no noise or had not wings or rockets.  recently the other person that was with me passed away.  i will go to my grave believing that what i saw was a ufo.
content.summary: Triangular craft about100 yds in diameter.  hovered then turned and moveddirectly over my car.  no sound.  small blister found on nose 2 days later.

content.detailedDescription:
Sometime in 2002 i was lying in bed, facing the window, trying to fall asleep. something that looked like a star entered into view quite quickly from the left side of the window. it stopped instantly, descended just as quickly, stopped instantly for a couple of seconds then shot out of sight to the right side of the window.
i didn't know what to think. i was having a hard time processing what i just saw. the next morning i told my husband about it and of course he thought i was crazy but i know what i saw. also a few nights later i was awaken by a deep,low, pulsating humming sound. kind of like a very strong electrical current. because i was half asleep, i didn't get out of bed. the room wasn't lit up or anything like that. i ended up falling back to sleep and recalled what i had heard the next morning.
content.flightPath: Straight-line path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Lying in bed facing the window. star like object flys into view from the left,stops,descends quickly, stops on a dime and shoots quickly out of sight

content.detailedDescription:
I was running late that morning to go to school at atlantic vocational
in coconut creek, florida.  i had to pick up my friend "d". we arrived at school and hurriedly walked up the very long side walk until half way and i noticed a very bright light in the sky. i told my friend "d" to look up and check it out. we stopped and stared at this bright light which was covered by clouds and it was not moving. it just hovered over the school. i started getting worried that maybe this thing was going to beam us up or something so i told my friend lets go. we continued on walking with our heads looking up the rest of the way until we reached the doors of the school. all of a sudden the door opened and my teacher grabbed my arm and said your late, i said look up in the sky and just then it disappeared. he saw it. we kept talking about it for awhile and then began our day when someone from upstairs called down to our classroom and asked if anyone had seen this glowing bright object hovering over the school. "d" and i said yes we saw it when walking up the walkway. we called the newspaper and they came out to the school to investigate and the whole school went out to the fields behind the school looking for any proof. after searching for about 15 minutes they found or so they say they found ( i think they planted it there) a weather balloon and that was the object that the school had seen. i don't think so, it was too bright to be some stupid weather balloon. i'm just glad that my friend and myself did not get taken or hurt. what i can't believe is that they tried making the whole school look stupid by saying it was a weather balloon.
[name removed/cms/tg]

i'm sorry i have no pictures from the 70s. we didn't have cell phones back then. i do think that you can find the newspaper article in the newspaper of broward county between 1976-1977.
content.summary: Walking up long side walk to school. whole school saw it.

content.detailedDescription:
My grandfather was bringing me home and i saw an object floating in the sky. i kept my eye on it until we got close to my house, when we pulled into my driveway my older sister was running home from her walk saying she was watching something in the sky, i said i had been watching it also. we looked in the sky at that time and could not see it. approx, 45 minutes later my mother, me a friend of mine and her mother were in our living room when we heard a low vibrating sound, woo woo woo woo, we stepped outside into the front yard looking to the sky, we kept walking toward the sidewalk looking up, it was daylight but close to dusk when we saw it hovering over our house the house next door and the driveway between them. it was round and it had large round pulsating lights around the whole bottom of it. we were froze but not frightened, i don't know how long we stood there, i don't believe we were  talking at all while we were staring at it. then it made no sound and lifted straight up into the air. we stood there and stared at each other for what seemed like several minutes after ward trying to wrap our heads around what we had just seen. later that evening when it had gotten dark we heard it again , my mother, myself father and sister  ran outside to see anything, but we saw nothing.
we never reported it, i was only in 7th grade but my mother and i talked about it on and off for the rest of her life because i just wanted to reconfirmed that i had seen what i'd seen and heard what i'd heard. she confirmed the same story every time. i know what i saw and i know what i heard. it was just above my house there was no way to mistake it for anything then what it was. we saw a lot of unusual lights and activity in the sky that summer but nothing as clear or as close as that.5
content.summary: Saw it from car. at home heard it went outside and witnessed it just above the house

content.detailedDescription: I was driving home from a college chemistry study hall, and i happened to look to my left in this field where i usually see deer. while i was driving i noticed a black car pulled over on the side if the road. suspecting that he was just observing some deer, i slowed down, pulled over, and look into the field. looking over i noticed a hovering disc almost egg-like aircraft hovering over the field. it was emitting a really warm heat and lights pulsing from purple to red, to red and back again. when i saw it i knew immediately it wasn't some lights or any weather related object. as i stared at it, i noticed that my radio started going staticky, my lights were flashing,and my engine was faltering. as i stared is hovered and then slowly started ascend until i lost sight of it. immediately after it left, my truck returned to normal. i returned home and told my parents who don't believe in aliens and such things, and told them. they told me that it was all in my head and to forget it. the whole experience left me thrilled and to be more of a believer. and
content.summary: Red/pink hovering ufo

content.detailedDescription:
Little mike, blue jay, and i were standing around the campfire when i noticed a light passing over the crest, then suddenly backed up very abruptly.  this caught our eye. we assumed it must be a helicopter,  but then it followed the ridge towards us.  as it  ame closer we soon realized that it was not a helicopter,  it was a flying saucer!  when it got close to our position, it broke away from the ridge and came directly to our fire and hovered over us slowly circling over our fire.  i could have hit it with a rock!  before it was over us blue jay began sceaming everything anyone had ever said about ufo's.  he was yelling: "rays, rays, they're gona shoot us with rays.  cattle mutelationswas", and things like that.  at first i was just in awe about what we were seeing, but after hearing blue jay sceam, i have to admit i was a little scared. i turned to little mike and asked:  "shoulders we hide?"  little mike respondd:  "i don't know,  what do you think? "  i said:  "where could we go it's only error us." i was with my friend "little mike" and a younger kid who lived in the village;  "blue jay".  blue jay was 13, little mike was 19, and i was 18 at the time.  after it  includes over us for around 15 minutes it slowed went behind the hill we were near and disappeared.  we trided looking into the trees trying to see anything, but we saw nothing. we sat around staring into the fire for some time.  no one said anything. the next thing i remember was falling into the fire. i lept up shocked that i had fallen into the fire. i was looking at my hands when little mike pro laimed:  "look".  it was the ufo coming out from behind the hill, but now it was lighter out and we could see the body of the craft, but the color of the lights was no longer discernable; the just looked like twinkling lights along the seem of the top and bottom of the craft. 
after it weaved it's way up the canyon,  we talked a little about it and decided not to report it, due to the fact.No one would believe us anyway.  to this day i have wondered what i saw.  we were in seddon village into the manzano mt. this is not far from the kirtland air force bace, so i have often wondered if it was a secret project or an real alien craft.  i can tell you this, it seemed pretty alien to us at the time. i couldn't believe how silent it was.  it was a totally clear calm night, not even a breeze.  it just seemed to float on air, no sound, no obvious propulsion.  it was so strange.  
what is really strange is that  a few weeks later i was telling someone a out it and he wanted to go look or it.  i assured him there was no way we would see it again, but at he insistence we went to the fire hills below sandia peak and unbelievably,  we saw it.  what are the odds of that?  that was over 30 years ago and i still think about it everyday.
content.flightPath: Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Spotted light our sandia crest,  that changed directing then came to us and circled over us, then went behind hill.  appeared later in morning and slowly went up the canyon.

   this event will remain etched in my mind until i pass.  thanks for allowing me to share this experience.

content.detailedDescription:
I left a poker game about 1:00 am. i drove to the end of the street and was going to turn left, when i looked to my right, i saw a huge disc shaped ufo with a dome just silently hovering in place. it was so huge that it had to be fairly close to the ground. cell phones were not in existence to call someone or take a photo. it was very bright and glowing white. it was very silent.

i didn't know what to do. i thought if i drove back to the house i had just left, by the time i alerted some friends and got back, the craft would be gone. i observed this ufo for at least 20 minutes, waiting for someone to drive by. no one came by. 

i know this may sound crazy, but i eventually just drove away. i drove west over  the bridge that opens for boat traffic on commercial blvd. in ft.Lauderdale and still saw the ufo just hovering in the same place to my right.

i saw a show about ufo's many years later and there was a ufo shown in miami that was the same exact craft i saw. it was white and glowing, disc shaped with a dome. i believe it was also in the mid nineteen eighties. i have that segment on tape from the tv. i am 67 years old now and was in my mid thirties at the time this happened.

there is a police station in lauderdale-by-the sea, that is just a couple of blocks from the sighting. i never checked with them. it would be hard for me to believe that no one in that police department ever heard of, or witnessed the same sighting i had witnessed. i know that i cannot be the only person that saw that craft because of the size of it, how it glowed so brightly, and how long it stayed stationary in one place. 


feel free to contact me if i could clarify things or help in any way.
content.summary: Glowing white ufo hovered. it was huge, saucer shaped with dome. no one came by. i drove away after 20 minutes

content.detailedDescription: It was a dark night. a few stars were visible above the horizon. we were stargazing and awed by the majestic sight. suddenly it seemed as if a lot of the stars were fading away. to our surprise suddenly an unidentifiable object moved into our sight. we thought it was very strange because it didn't look like anything we had ever seen before. of course; we tried to take a picture, but suddenly all of our electronic devices jammed or stopped working altogether. shocked, we took out our compass, but it spun around uncontrollably. we felt like we couldn't do anything but watch, as if our minds were clouded by its presence. after some minutes (which occurred to us as hours) the object flew away again. we noticed that our mobiles were working again and that the object had only been there for thirteen minutes and 37 seconds!!! we decided that it would be the best to report this incident immediately.
content.summary: An ufo came and hovered a few minutes before leaving again

content.detailedDescription: I went to visit my mother, who lives at 411 n. stewart ave. norman oklahoma 73069. it was march 25th 2011 good friday. about 7:00p. there had been these strange mamatized clouds in the sky all day long proceeding the sighting. i've never seen clouds like this above norman before or since then. and i had lived here 25 years before this. it was warm, and mom wanted to walk around the yard and talk as she often enjoyed doing. there was strange silent cloud to cloud lightning going on by now. it was just about to be dark,twilight. but still plenty of light to see the object. when there was a flash of lightning directly over head, it made no sound but something made me look up in the direction of it. this is when i first saw it, it was a flat black, boomerang shaped object. it was completely featureless, no lights, and completely silent. in fact when it flew over, things suddenly became extra quiet, no birds, no wind, nothing. and i new from the vary first moment i saw it that i was having an authentic sighting. this area is in the middle of a residential area. what was it doing here? is what i remember thinking. i saw it for about 45 seconds as it flew over moms house going from n.E.E. to s.W.W. it was shaped like a boomerang but it was pointing to the s.E.E.In opposition to the direction of flight. it was about 45 seconds before i could get mom to see it. but when she did she exclaimed, what is that. she does not like to talk about it, but she saw the object for about 45 seconds before it flew out of sight. it was about 125 ft. high or skirting the bottom of the clouds. i have no pictures but could draw the object. the total time of the sighting took about 1min. 15 seconds. i saw the object the whole time, mom only saw the object for about 45 seconds.
content.summary: Flat black, boomerang, chevron shaped object flew over sighting sight slowly, silently. from north east east to south west west in a straight line under and through ionized clouds.

content.detailedDescription:
The encounter began 01/02/12, at 1:37 am. i was out looking for my cat, in which never returned. i look up at the south side of my home. on top of the mountain, i see eight white lights gathering to form a circle. they sit for about 5 seconds in a circle, then by the speed of light, two lights go south, two lights go east, two lights go west, and then two lights in a very slow speed go north in alignment. as i watch they continue going north until they reach the mountain area north of us. at this point it stops. the light in the front beams a light down, in which it was so bright that i could see the light threw all the trees, about a quarter mile distant. months later i encounter my new neighbor, in which lives about a quarter mile up the road. she states to me "did you see that white light a few months ago?" i replied "what do you mean". wanting to be sure that she was talking about the same thing i was, and i didn't go making a fool of myself. she then went into description, in which was what i saw. she stated, "it was very close to our house". boy did she feel relieved and didn't feel as if she was going crazy after i told her i saw it too. 

you may want to look at the weather patterns, and take note of the change since 01/02/12. where that light beamed down, the sun may hit at different angles, different times of the year and possibly controlling the weather.

there have been other encounters here of other flying objects from many people, as well. what ever it is all individuals from miles around describe it as a cigar shape with many different colored lights, with a vacuum, vibrating, humming noise, and always at night.
content.summary: Eight white lights: gathering to form circle, then splitting apart. then beaming white light down.

content.detailedDescription: around 8pm walking down driveway toward house, i stopped to look at stars as usual. looking to west/southwest about 45 degrees up i saw a bright star, but quickly revised my view to a planet, but knew there should not be a planet there(i am a space techie and former usaf weather observer)! as i continued to watch it got brighter and brighter and larger fast and i mean fast like less than a minute(approx.) and i began running down the driveway to front of house as its path seemed to be headed in that direction. i saw a neighbor walking (east to west)toward me.I asked her if she was seeing what i was seeing and she said yes and commented on how fast it was moving. it suddenly stopped just above our road just above tree height. it was all white like gleaming, somewhat egg shaped, but clearly over 6ft tall and approx.50ft long. it almost appeared to turn around and then shot back somewhat to the west, very very fast. fast like faster than the f4's from my base! i  was so astounded that i never thought about anything but seeing it for as long as i could. i ran inside and reported it on my computer to a sight supposedly there for reporting such sights. and i have been captivated by it ever since, hopping it would come back and trying to refine the shape of it.
content.summary: 1 looked like star(bright) then planet, but keeped getting brighter

content.detailedDescription: A couple of friends and i were walking when we saw a bunch of different flashing lights i noticed they were stacked above each other on 3 different levels flashing colors top row flashing one color while the other 2 rows flashing different colors they moved across the sky slowly just flashing after 10 or15 minutes moving west to east moving towards us over us then away from us then they all came together to form one giant orb then shot across the sky instantly disappear in the distance the next day i saw in the dayton daily newspaper that we were not the only ones to see this event but after a couple of days it was never talked about again
content.summary: Saw 6 to 8 separate colored flashing lights stacked moving west to east then all came together formed a giant orb and instantly shot out of sight
